        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=15853&TOPIC_ID=2180&FORUM_ID=3&CAT_ID=1&Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&Topic_Title=Advice&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> I have a played a while (having 2 characters over 50 th lvl -one is a wizz) so I have some suggestions for you-<BR>I recently started a erudite necro and have had a blast since..<BR>If you didnt already know all the dots stack. So hit the mob with darkness line then pet will attack then dot him with as many as ya got and if your pets health reaches 50 % or so run in and help him out (dont go craazy and die). </P><P> Make hotkeys for all pet commands-example /pet attack /pet back off /pet guard here /pet follow me /pet sit down /pet stand up /pet guard me <<<--i think that last one is right, and save any weapons you get from mobs to give him.  All low lvl spells can be bought in your hometown --lvl 12 spells, 4 of them i believe are bought elsewhere---underground quenos or freeport underground.  Again im only lvl 13 so thats all i really know.</P><P>I killed knolls till my faction was good with quenos so i can enter the city above and also the evil catacombs below.  I got tired of grouping so this is a fun class to play alone (resist the urge to speak to your pet ....he wont respond)</P><P>So far im having a blast, you will be respected when you alone can take a camp where it would take a group of 3 or 4 to do the same camp.<BR>There are also many new quests in neriak i understand for us necros<BR>so look them up on allakzam</P><P></P><P><BR>                  Darkomens Necromancer Of the 12th Season<BR>                         Cazic Thule-My Lord And God</P><P><BR> [quote]Keep your friends close, but keep your enemies closer</P><P></P><P>Edited by - orion61269 on 03/30/2002  17:37:59<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
